I took some shortcuts in writing this but the basic logic should be sound


Counter EQU #-0
Cycles EQU #100
DUTY EQU #0
DutyModifier EQU #1
MaxBrightness EQU #100


Top NOP


LDR R7, =Cycles
LDR R6, R7  ;R6 = Cycles
LDR R7, =DUTY
LDR R5, R7 ; R5 = DUTY
LDR R7, =DutyModifier
LDR R4, R7 ;R4 = DutyModifier
LDR R7, =Counter
LDR R3, R7 ; R3 = Counter
LDR R7, =MaxBrightness
LDR R8, R7

ADD R2, R3, R5 ;Duty goes from 0 to max brightness so if duty is greater than counter then it's on this cycle
BV Negative
LED on
B Positive
Negative NOP
LED off
Positive NOP


ADD R3, R3, #-1
ADD R2, R7, Counter
BZP NoReset
MOV R3, #0
ADD R5, R5, R7

ADD R2, R5, R8
BVP newTest
NOT R4, R4
ADD R4, R4, #1
B NoReset
newTest ADD R2, R5, #0
BNV NoReset
NOT R4, R4
ADD R4, R4, #1
NoReset NOP

B Top
